# No AWS deploy (default)

Until the user **explicitly** says otherwise, **never deploy or push to AWS**.

## Do not run

- `npm run deploy:api` or `npm run deploy:api:guided`
- `sam deploy` (any variant)
- AWS CLI commands that create, update, or delete cloud resources (stacks, Lambda, DynamoDB tables, S3 buckets, SSM parameters, etc.)
- Suggesting or offering to deploy to AWS without being asked

## Allowed without override

- Local development: `npm run start:api`, `sam local start-api`, `sam build`, DynamoDB Local, LocalStack
- `npm run test:api` and `npm run test:api:deployed` (only when the user supplies `HUB_API_URL` / credentials)
- Documentation and code changes for AWS deploy tooling
- `git push` to GitHub (not AWS)

## Override

Only deploy to AWS when the user clearly requests it (e.g. "deploy to AWS", "run deploy:api", or "push to AWS").
